In [8]:
for i in range(data.shape[0]):
    data.at[i, 'sex'] = data.at[i, 'sex'].upper()
    data.at[i, 'Pstatus'] = data.at[i, 'Pstatus'].upper()
    
    for letter in ['M', 'F']:
        if data.at[i, f'{letter}edu'] == 'o':
            data.at[i, f'{letter}edu'] = '0'
        data.at[i, f'{letter}edu'] = int(data.at[i, f'{letter}edu'])
        data.at[i, f'{letter}job'] = data.at[i, f'{letter}job'].replace('-', '_')
        
    if data.at[i, 'guardian'] == 'futher':
        data.at[i, 'guardian'] = 'father'
        
data.Medu = data.Medu.astype('int64')
data.Fedu = data.Fedu.astype('int64')

outliers = {}

for column in numeric_data[1:]:
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1  #IQR    

    filter_ = (data[column] >= Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) & (data[column] <= Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)  #   

    outliers[column] = data.shape[0] - data.loc[filter_].shape[0]  #   -
    
print(outliers)

def delete_dupl(df):
    return df.drop_duplicates(subset=list(set(df.columns) - set(['ID', 'Subject', 'failures', 'paid', 'G1', 'G2', 'G3'])))

In [70]:
def mark(m: int):
    if 18 <= m <= 20:
        return 'Excellent'
    elif 14 <= m <= 17:
        return 'Good'
    elif 8 <= m <= 13:
        return 'Satisfactory'
    elif m < 8:
        return 'Unsatisfactory'
    
data['mark'] = [mark(x) for x in data.G3]

In [75]:
def is_similar(row1, row2):
    for col in avail:
        if row1[col] != row2[col]:
            return False
    return True
In [76]:
similar = pd.DataFrame(columns=['new_id'] + list(data.columns))

t = 0
new_id = 0

for i in range(len(data) - 1):
    for j in range(len(data) - 1):
        if i != j and is_similar(data.loc[i], data.loc[j]):
            similar.loc[t] = [new_id] + list(data.loc[i])
            t += 1
            similar.loc[t] = [new_id] + list(data.loc[j])
            t += 1
            new_id += 1
